05:32.856 --> 05:34.624
Docket 3942.

05:34.658 --> 05:37.126
People of the state of Illinois
vs. Alvin Olinsky,

05:37.161 --> 05:39.662
single count of murder
in the second degree

05:39.696 --> 05:41.798
and felony concealment of a homicide.

05:41.832 --> 05:43.900
Your honor, Peter Manetti
for the defendant.

05:43.934 --> 05:45.301
How does your client plead?

05:45.326 --> 05:46.803
Not guilty.

05:46.837 --> 05:48.471
I'd like to request that
the defendant be released

05:48.505 --> 05:50.239
on his own recognizance.

05:50.274 --> 05:51.674
He's a decorated police officer,

05:51.708 --> 05:53.209
- with over 30 ye...
- Bond hearing

05:53.243 --> 05:55.745
is in two days, counselor.
Give your speech then.

05:55.779 --> 06:00.016
- [gavel bangs]
- Next case.

06:00.050 --> 06:02.318
Come with me.

06:02.352 --> 06:04.353
Al, Al, please.

06:04.388 --> 06:07.824
- You've gotta end this now.
- Let's go.

06:07.858 --> 06:10.760
Docket Number 4523, people of the state

06:10.794 --> 06:12.995
of Illinois vs. Donald Odem.

06:13.030 --> 06:15.064
Three counts of felony battery.

06:15.099 --> 06:18.034
- All parties present?
- Yes, Your Honor.

06:24.808 --> 06:26.542
So, you ready to talk, Hank?

06:26.577 --> 06:28.211
You know Olinksy's innocent.

06:28.245 --> 06:30.746
You know he didn't kill
that piece of garbage, Bingham.

06:30.781 --> 06:33.416
Oh, yeah? Then who did?

06:35.719 --> 06:39.822
Olinsky flips or he rots in prison.

06:47.564 --> 06:50.133
I know, I know.

06:50.167 --> 06:52.101
Beige isn't my color.

06:52.136 --> 06:53.536
Well...

06:53.570 --> 06:55.404
You're not gonna have
to wear it long, I promise.

06:55.439 --> 06:57.807
Nah, I'm good.

06:57.841 --> 06:59.909
I mean, they don't have a case.

06:59.943 --> 07:02.778
The evidence is weak. We all know that.

07:02.813 --> 07:05.314
I'll make bail. We go from there.

07:05.349 --> 07:07.049
Okay, listen.

07:07.084 --> 07:08.584
I'm hiring a lawyer.

07:08.619 --> 07:10.386
- I'm getting you out of here.
- I don't want that.

07:10.420 --> 07:12.722
Al... I don't really care what you want.

07:12.756 --> 07:15.291
Listen, man, just make sure I get bail.

07:15.325 --> 07:16.926
All right? That's all I ask.

07:18.595 --> 07:20.229
I mean, we've been through worse.

07:20.264 --> 07:23.900
And every time, we find a way
through to the other side.

07:23.934 --> 07:26.435
All right? Listen, man,
this is no different.

07:26.470 --> 07:29.672
Yeah. Listen. I appreciate
your loyalty, but...

07:29.706 --> 07:32.341
Hey, we're gonna... We can beat this.

07:32.376 --> 07:34.410
We will beat it.

07:34.444 --> 07:36.979
All right? It's Chicago.

07:39.783 --> 07:42.785
I need something.

07:42.819 --> 07:44.987
- Olinsky.
- Listen, the bail hearing

07:45.022 --> 07:47.190
is in two days. I mean, I don't care

07:47.224 --> 07:49.425
what the number is.

07:49.459 --> 07:51.661
I just need to make sure he gets out.

07:53.297 --> 07:55.631
Talking about murder here, Hank.

07:55.666 --> 07:57.800
We're talking about a cop here, Tommy.

07:57.834 --> 07:58.668
Yeah.

07:58.702 --> 08:01.971
These days, that might work against him.

08:02.005 --> 08:03.606
You know what the hell
it's like out there.

08:03.640 --> 08:06.776
I don't care what it's like.
You understand?

08:06.810 --> 08:09.111
I just need to make sure
he gets released.

08:09.146 --> 08:11.147
No.

08:11.181 --> 08:12.782
I need you...

08:12.816 --> 08:16.953
to make sure he gets released.

08:16.987 --> 08:19.488
Hank, this is a really hard ask.

08:19.523 --> 08:21.324
You know what's a hard ask?

08:21.358 --> 08:22.959
Hmm?

08:22.993 --> 08:25.494
Looking the other way
when a respected judge

08:25.529 --> 08:28.831
shoots a drug dealer in cold blood.

08:34.104 --> 08:35.804
Yeah.

08:35.839 --> 08:38.307
He killed my daughter.
He got what he deserved.

08:38.342 --> 08:40.643
Yeah, I know. And I agree.

08:40.677 --> 08:43.179
That's why you got a pass.

08:47.851 --> 08:49.885
Tommy...

08:49.920 --> 08:52.989
I need this. You understand? So...

08:53.023 --> 08:56.380
Whatever you have to do, just...

08:57.561 --> 09:00.029
make sure Al makes bail.

09:08.705 --> 09:10.906
- Any update, Sarge?
- Yep, bond hearing's

09:10.941 --> 09:13.276
in two days. He'll be released then.

09:13.310 --> 09:15.544
I don't know about that.

09:17.080 --> 09:18.581
Well, I do.

09:18.615 --> 09:21.117
I said, he'll be released then.

09:25.055 --> 09:27.089
Any more questions?

09:27.124 --> 09:29.025
Now's the time.

09:31.928 --> 09:33.863
Listen...

09:33.897 --> 09:36.746
I'm not gonna lie. It has been...

09:37.968 --> 09:40.069
a tough day.

09:41.672 --> 09:44.540
But we still have jobs to do, right?

09:44.574 --> 09:47.009
The world continues to turn.

09:47.978 --> 09:49.412
So.

09:49.446 --> 09:51.147
Who's got an update on these M4s?

09:51.181 --> 09:53.883
I just talked to Halstead.
He confirmed Dexter

09:53.917 --> 09:55.551
did not have the guns in his possession.

09:55.585 --> 09:57.486
They were supposed to be
dropped off yesterday,

09:57.521 --> 09:59.121
but his connect in Indiana got hung up.

09:59.156 --> 10:00.723
They will be dropped off today.

10:00.757 --> 10:03.159
Okay. Do we know who his connect is?

10:03.193 --> 10:04.894
- Not at this point.
- All right, Atwater,

10:04.928 --> 10:07.229
These bangers you're hanging
with, do they trust you?

10:07.264 --> 10:10.099
Yeah, Shabazz does. I saved his life.

10:10.133 --> 10:13.602
Well, I was the guy holding
the gun threatening him, but.

10:13.637 --> 10:16.906
So, how about we
get this deal back on track?

10:16.940 --> 10:18.841
Okay, well, they answer
to this dude named Wes.

10:18.875 --> 10:20.776
Wes calls all the shots.

10:20.811 --> 10:22.745
And his boys just got punked
by some white dudes,

10:22.779 --> 10:25.981
so he's hot as hell, but... I got it.

10:26.016 --> 10:27.516
Good.

10:27.551 --> 10:30.152
- You good?
- Yeah, uh-huh.

10:30.187 --> 10:32.822
So wait a minute, you want me
to overlook what happened?

10:32.856 --> 10:34.357
Just smile? Turn the other cheek

10:34.391 --> 10:35.991
and let them boys just piss all over us?

10:36.026 --> 10:37.593
Homie, I ain't never sayin' that.

10:37.627 --> 10:39.328
- Then what you sayin', then?
- What is you sayin'?

10:39.363 --> 10:40.663
Why we even discussing this?

10:40.697 --> 10:43.165
They played us like some damn fools.

10:43.200 --> 10:45.034
I say we go over there
and do what's right.

10:45.068 --> 10:46.669
What, you wanna start killing people?

10:46.703 --> 10:47.870
- You damn right.
- There's no profit in that.

10:47.904 --> 10:49.171
And it'll bring too much heat.

10:49.206 --> 10:50.439
Well, at least let me square away

10:50.474 --> 10:51.974
the white boy, Nate.

10:52.008 --> 10:54.210
Cracker think it's okay
to violate me like that, us?

10:54.244 --> 10:55.978
Look, I know you ain't askin' me, Wes,

10:56.012 --> 10:57.980
but I feel like we missing
a big move right here.

10:58.014 --> 10:59.882
Now why would we get revenge,
when we could just use

10:59.916 --> 11:02.051
that whole situation,
that whole beat-down,

11:02.085 --> 11:04.653
as some kind of
bargaining chip or something?

11:04.688 --> 11:06.789
Let me go over there and talk to Dexter.

11:06.823 --> 11:08.858
I'll tell him that you pissed off.

11:08.892 --> 11:10.626
Naturally he expected you to clap back,

11:10.660 --> 11:12.862
but you smarter than that, right?

11:12.896 --> 11:14.864
You ain't no bitch. You a business man,

11:14.898 --> 11:16.365
and a business man
is willing to overlook

11:16.400 --> 11:18.501
this whole Malik situation,
if he down to give

11:18.535 --> 11:20.136
you a discount on the heaters,

11:20.170 --> 11:22.004
and do the whole deal
right here in your club

11:22.038 --> 11:24.140
where you comfortable.
Come on, boy, we win.

11:24.174 --> 11:27.710
- [laughs]
- That's what's up.

11:29.045 --> 11:31.013
What, is you serious? Y'all serious?

11:31.047 --> 11:33.749
I'm gonna need you to back off.

11:33.784 --> 11:36.051
No retaliation, no nothing. We clear?

11:36.086 --> 11:38.421
Yo, my man. I'm supposed to just

11:38.455 --> 11:40.189
let him talk to me
like some type of bitch?

11:40.223 --> 11:40.956
Malik.

11:40.991 --> 11:43.893
I ain't gon' ask you again, man.

11:45.796 --> 11:48.330
Are we clear?

11:50.600 --> 11:52.535
Yeah, we clear.

11:52.569 --> 11:54.370
Loud and clear.

11:57.541 --> 11:59.041
Cool.

11:59.075 --> 12:00.509
Let me hit Dexter now.

12:00.544 --> 12:02.411
No. I'll hit him up.

12:02.446 --> 12:04.980
I'm tired of dealing
with the middle man.

12:06.249 --> 12:08.884
All right, as long as I
get my cut, I ain't trippin'.

12:08.919 --> 12:10.519
Oh, you gon' get your cut.

12:10.554 --> 12:12.488
I'm a man of my word.

12:23.233 --> 12:25.801
I'm impressed.
No way I thought Wes would

12:25.836 --> 12:27.203
still be open to doing business.

12:27.237 --> 12:28.938
I told you, man. He's smart.

12:28.972 --> 12:32.074
He ain't that smart.
Even with the 20% discount,

12:32.108 --> 12:35.311
dumbass is still paying 50% over market.

12:35.345 --> 12:36.712
It's good, though.

12:36.746 --> 12:38.214
You know, if this works out,

12:38.248 --> 12:41.116
we can use Wes to distribute
to the other black gangs.

12:41.151 --> 12:43.052
So what's up, the guns
are inside with Nate?

12:43.086 --> 12:45.054
That's not your concern.

12:45.088 --> 12:47.823
I'm just trying to make sure
we do the deal right.

12:47.858 --> 12:49.558
This time, anyway.

12:49.593 --> 12:52.795
Relax, it's all gonna work out.

12:59.803 --> 13:01.937
Yo, Nate!

13:06.142 --> 13:07.910
Yo, Nate!

13:07.944 --> 13:10.980
Let's go, man, it's game time!

13:14.951 --> 13:17.920
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

13:17.954 --> 13:19.455
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:19.489 --> 13:22.258
Yo, check this out.

13:22.292 --> 13:29.098
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:29.833 --> 13:31.700
Those punks want to start a war,

13:31.735 --> 13:34.436
they came to the right place.

13:34.471 --> 13:38.974
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:51.095 --> 13:53.396
They're supposed to be here an hour ago.

13:53.421 --> 13:55.050
Yeah, yeah, yeah. I know, we got you.

13:55.084 --> 13:56.551
Keep telling y'all.

13:56.585 --> 13:58.461
Dudes don't respect nothing.
They can't be trusted.

13:58.486 --> 14:00.121
- Let me do this, man.
- Got it.

14:00.156 --> 14:01.956
I got it. Ryan?

14:01.991 --> 14:05.060
What the hell is goin' on, man?
We waitin' on you, bro.

14:06.996 --> 14:08.863
All right.

14:08.898 --> 14:10.565
What happened?

14:10.599 --> 14:12.400
That deal ain't going down today.

14:12.435 --> 14:14.669
Why not?

14:15.638 --> 14:18.006
Nate just popped up dead.

14:20.910 --> 14:22.877
Please tell me

14:22.912 --> 14:24.979
you ain't as stupid as I think you are.

14:25.014 --> 14:27.566
Hell no, I ain't had
nothing to do with that.

14:28.332 --> 14:30.972
- You sure about that?
- I'm positive!

14:31.502 --> 14:33.903
You asked permission earlier today

14:33.938 --> 14:37.307
to pop off some cracker-ass
gun seller named Nate.

14:37.341 --> 14:39.776
And tonight, that same
cracker-ass gun seller

14:39.810 --> 14:41.811
wind up dead, and it ain't got
nothin' to do with you?

14:41.846 --> 14:44.948
Wes, chill man.

14:44.982 --> 14:47.651
It is what it is, man.
It's just a coincidence.

14:47.685 --> 14:50.086
Well, I don't believe
in coincidence, man.

14:52.189 --> 14:55.258
Shabazz, you... you believe
in coincidence, man?

14:55.293 --> 14:57.527
Not sure, all right?

14:57.561 --> 14:59.329
Man, I know Malik didn't do the murder.

14:59.363 --> 15:02.432
- Why you say that?
- 'Cause you told him not to.

15:02.466 --> 15:05.135
All right, 'cause I was
with him all day.

15:05.169 --> 15:07.270
Never left my sight.

15:07.305 --> 15:11.841
And I ain't seen him kill
no white boy named Nate.

15:13.744 --> 15:16.880
Yo! Wes, I didn't do it, man!

15:16.914 --> 15:19.849
You better hope... You better hope

15:19.884 --> 15:21.484
he's telling the truth, man.

15:21.519 --> 15:23.386
[pained grunt]

15:23.421 --> 15:26.389
<i>[sinister music]</i>

15:26.424 --> 15:33.697
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:35.666 --> 15:37.967
Of course Malik didn't cop to it.

15:38.002 --> 15:40.003
Man swore up and down
he had nothing to do with it.

15:40.037 --> 15:41.338
Almost convincing, too.

15:41.372 --> 15:44.007
- You believe him?
- Not for a second.

15:44.041 --> 15:45.342
All right, so let's get a search warrant

15:45.376 --> 15:46.676
for Malik's house.

15:46.711 --> 15:47.911
Maybe we find some blood, a gun.

15:47.945 --> 15:49.713
Build a murder case that way.

15:49.747 --> 15:51.414
We go in now, we blow Atwater's cover.

15:51.449 --> 15:53.917
I know, but, you know,
we're talking murder.

15:53.951 --> 15:56.920
I'm not gonna blow
a major gun case on a "maybe."

15:56.954 --> 15:58.822
So now what? Sit back and wait

15:58.856 --> 16:00.824
for Dexter and his boys
to start a gang war?

16:00.858 --> 16:02.726
Well, hopefully he's too smart for that.

16:02.760 --> 16:04.694
I'm not so sure, Sarge.

16:04.729 --> 16:06.096
- He had fire in his eyes.
- [phone buzzing]

16:06.130 --> 16:07.897
He said he was gonna
kill everybody involved.

16:07.932 --> 16:09.366
Talk to him.

16:09.400 --> 16:12.369
Persuade him to think
like a businessman.

16:12.403 --> 16:14.204
Hey, man.

16:17.942 --> 16:20.143
Got your own private room.

16:26.650 --> 16:29.319
Hopefully you won't be here long.

16:29.920 --> 16:31.888
Look, you probably know this, but cops

16:31.922 --> 16:34.357
are targets around here,
so I'm gonna personally

16:34.392 --> 16:36.226
do what I can to help out.

16:36.260 --> 16:38.862
I always wanted to be a cop myself.

16:38.896 --> 16:40.230
Corrections was the next best thing.

16:40.264 --> 16:42.732
- Right.
- Oh, one more thing.

16:42.767 --> 16:44.067
You don't wanna eat the food,

16:44.101 --> 16:47.337
because these animals
are gonna piss in it.

16:51.442 --> 16:53.443
Thanks.

16:53.944 --> 16:56.012
I got your back.

17:16.099 --> 17:19.935
- [slamming on bars]
- So you're the pig?

17:19.970 --> 17:21.905
It's coming.

17:21.939 --> 17:24.073
Just a matter of time.

17:25.276 --> 17:28.611
And we're gonna find your wife, too.

17:28.646 --> 17:31.214
[grunting in pain]

17:33.017 --> 17:35.585
You ever mention
my wife again, I'll kill you.

17:35.619 --> 17:37.987
- Hey! Back it up!
- I'll kill you, I'll kill you.

17:38.022 --> 17:39.255
- Let him go!
- I'll kill you.

17:39.290 --> 17:41.357
- Let him go!
- I'll kill you.

17:41.392 --> 17:44.360
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:44.395 --> 17:51.267
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:57.341 --> 18:00.143
Hey.

18:00.177 --> 18:02.345
There's good news. I just got word

18:02.379 --> 18:04.180
that Judge Gladchuck is in charge

18:04.215 --> 18:05.648
of bail hearings tomorrow.

18:05.683 --> 18:07.684
Gladchuck? He's a hard-ass.

18:07.718 --> 18:09.152
I know.

18:09.186 --> 18:11.354
Tomorrow, he's not gonna be there.

18:11.388 --> 18:13.122
He's gonna contract the stomach flu.

18:13.157 --> 18:15.191
- The really bad kind.
- Ah.

18:15.226 --> 18:17.494
Fever, nausea, the whole thing.

18:17.528 --> 18:20.196
- Oh, that's a shame.
- Yeah.

18:20.231 --> 18:22.866
It's probably not gonna hit him
till 8:55 or so,

18:22.900 --> 18:26.536
just before court convenes,
at which point he'll reach out,

18:26.570 --> 18:31.441
ask me to cover for him.
And I will graciously agree.

18:32.343 --> 18:34.878
You sure he's gonna come through?

18:36.046 --> 18:38.248
Doesn't have a choice.

18:38.282 --> 18:40.383
You got something on him.

18:41.085 --> 18:43.419
I got something on everybody.

18:43.454 --> 18:45.522
Just like you.

18:49.760 --> 18:51.494
Thanks, Tommy.

18:53.531 --> 18:56.900
- Spring in Chicago, huh?
- Yeah.

18:59.236 --> 19:00.503
Say what you said one more time, Ryan.

19:00.538 --> 19:02.038
Say what you said one more time, Ryan,

19:02.072 --> 19:03.172
'cause I don't think I heard you right.

19:03.207 --> 19:04.674
So say it one more time.

19:04.708 --> 19:08.044
I think you should still
do the deal with Wes' crew.

19:08.078 --> 19:10.580
And ignore the fact
they killed my cousin?

19:11.815 --> 19:14.083
I didn't say that.

19:15.753 --> 19:18.087
All right, hold up.

19:19.423 --> 19:21.925
Let's say they did the murder.

19:21.959 --> 19:23.393
You're gonna get revenge,
you're gonna do it

19:23.427 --> 19:26.262
after we do the deal, not before.

19:26.297 --> 19:29.365
You got, what, seven days
to pay off the supplier?

19:29.400 --> 19:30.900
And what has that got
to do with anything?

19:30.935 --> 19:32.602
Right, if you go cowboy
and you pop Malik

19:32.636 --> 19:35.238
or you pop Shabazz, the cops
are gonna be all over you.

19:35.272 --> 19:37.574
Then you can't line up a new buyer,

19:37.608 --> 19:40.343
which means you can't
pay off the supplier.

19:45.449 --> 19:48.484
Shabazz, what up, dog?

19:48.519 --> 19:51.321
So, uh, it's kinda early
to be drinking vodka,

19:51.355 --> 19:53.423
but whatever.
I already rapped with Ryan.

19:53.457 --> 19:55.258
All right, he talked it up with Dexter,

19:55.292 --> 19:56.492
and Dexter's still down to do the deal.

19:56.527 --> 19:58.161
Okay? Regardless of what happen

19:58.195 --> 20:00.463
to his cousin,
we in it for good money, baby.

20:01.198 --> 20:02.498
- Yeah.
- All right.

20:02.533 --> 20:04.767
So why you trippin', bro? You good?

20:04.802 --> 20:06.869
'Cause Dexter made a new demand.

20:07.605 --> 20:10.773
Told Wes the only way
he'd move forward is if

20:10.808 --> 20:13.242
he evened things out.

20:13.277 --> 20:15.011
Evened things out...
what are you talking about?

20:15.045 --> 20:17.747
The bodies.

20:17.781 --> 20:20.083
Wes saying Malik has to go.

20:21.885 --> 20:23.753
And I gotta do it.

20:25.356 --> 20:27.991
- Wait, what?
- Yeah.

20:29.159 --> 20:30.627
I have to kill my little brother.

20:30.661 --> 20:32.261
No, no, you gotta walk away...

20:32.296 --> 20:35.031
It don't work that way.

20:35.065 --> 20:36.799
You know that.

20:36.834 --> 20:39.802
<i>[somber music]</i>

20:39.837 --> 20:47.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:53.217 --> 20:55.818
I know you think this is gonna go away.

20:55.853 --> 20:57.854
But it's not.

20:57.888 --> 20:59.856
You need to wake up.

20:59.890 --> 21:02.492
This is your life.

21:02.526 --> 21:04.694
If you don't tell the truth
about what happened,

21:04.728 --> 21:06.162
you will die in prison.

21:06.196 --> 21:07.830
Look, I don't wanna talk about this now.

21:07.865 --> 21:09.132
Why?

21:09.166 --> 21:10.800
Well, you don't understand.

21:10.834 --> 21:12.702
I d-don't understand what?

21:12.736 --> 21:14.170
You don't understand me.

21:14.204 --> 21:15.638
I do. Trust me.

21:15.673 --> 21:17.173
All right, then why
do you keep asking me

21:17.207 --> 21:19.042
to do something that I'm not capable of?

21:19.076 --> 21:22.345
Why?

21:22.379 --> 21:26.749
'Cause despite everything
we have been through,

21:26.784 --> 21:28.584
I still love you.

21:28.619 --> 21:32.722
And I just want you to love yourself.

21:32.756 --> 21:34.490
Just a little.

21:35.292 --> 21:38.428
Just enough to make you realize
how stupid it is

21:38.462 --> 21:41.597
to sacrifice your life for Hank Voight.

21:41.632 --> 21:44.734
Listen, honey. Please, I love you.

21:44.768 --> 21:48.204
And I know you're trying
to look out for me.

21:48.238 --> 21:50.740
But I'm gonna beat this. I am.

21:51.575 --> 21:54.377
But I'm gonna beat it the right way,

21:54.411 --> 21:56.813
the only way that I know how.

22:04.722 --> 22:06.089
Hey, man.

22:06.123 --> 22:08.958
Here to see Alvin Olinksy.

22:08.992 --> 22:10.693
You're too late.

22:10.728 --> 22:13.696
Listen, I'm Sergeant
Hank Voight, Intelligence.

22:13.731 --> 22:15.131
Just wanna say hello to a friend.

22:15.165 --> 22:16.733
Sorry, inmate visiting hours are over.

22:16.767 --> 22:18.901
Yeah, well, he's not
an inmate, he's a cop.

22:18.936 --> 22:21.471
If he's in here, he's an inmate.

22:21.505 --> 22:23.740
Hey.

22:23.774 --> 22:26.576
Hey.

22:26.610 --> 22:29.078
- You sure there's nothing...
- I'm sure.

22:29.113 --> 22:30.913
But feel free to swing by
tomorrow morning.

22:30.948 --> 22:33.449
Meredith. How's Al?

22:34.451 --> 22:37.253
Hey. Come on, talk to me.

22:37.287 --> 22:38.988
It should be you in there.

22:39.022 --> 22:41.257
Not him.

22:41.291 --> 22:44.293
And it makes me sick.

22:44.328 --> 22:46.763
I wish he was just a regular guy,

22:46.797 --> 22:50.600
not someone who lived
by some stupid code.

22:50.634 --> 22:53.536
Would make everything so much easier.

22:56.340 --> 22:58.307
[door slams]

23:05.992 --> 23:07.959
Hey. Any update on Al?

23:07.993 --> 23:09.489
Case is all over the news.

23:09.514 --> 23:11.129
Yeah, I think that's to be
expected, Hailey.

23:11.163 --> 23:12.857
I just hope the judge gives him bail.

23:12.882 --> 23:13.882
He will.

23:13.907 --> 23:16.326
Well, statute for murder
is pretty tough.

23:16.351 --> 23:18.686
Well, I said he will.

23:18.720 --> 23:21.789
Listen, I'm done talking
about Al, understand?

23:23.558 --> 23:25.492
Somebody wanna talk about these M4s,

23:25.527 --> 23:27.327
I'm happy to engage.

23:27.362 --> 23:29.029
- Mm.
- Well,

23:29.064 --> 23:31.532
the whole operation just got
a lot more complicated.

23:31.566 --> 23:32.566
What do you mean?

23:32.600 --> 23:33.867
Wes just ordered Shabazz

23:33.902 --> 23:35.569
to kill his little brother, Malik.

23:35.603 --> 23:36.770
Huh.

23:36.805 --> 23:38.839
Dexter say that's the only
way he's gonna do the deal.

23:38.873 --> 23:40.708
All right,
so where's Shabazz on all this?

23:40.742 --> 23:42.543
He gonna carry out the order?

23:42.577 --> 23:44.311
Of course he's not gonna
carry out the order.

23:44.345 --> 23:46.246
He doesn't wanna
kill his little brother.

23:46.281 --> 23:47.715
But Wes told him to do it.

23:47.749 --> 23:49.750
So if Shabazz doesn't
kill Malik, then...

23:49.784 --> 23:51.552
Wes kills Shabazz, simple as that.

23:51.586 --> 23:53.587
Doesn't sound simple to me.

23:53.621 --> 23:54.888
We can't let this man take out

23:54.923 --> 23:57.191
his own flesh and blood, not like that.

23:57.225 --> 23:59.793
Why not?

24:02.363 --> 24:03.697
- Excuse me?
- We're about to take

24:03.732 --> 24:05.833
some serious guns off the street.

24:05.867 --> 24:09.069
Guns capable of killing a lot
of innocent civilians.

24:09.104 --> 24:11.405
The cost of doing that
is losing one gang-banger...

24:11.439 --> 24:12.840
[scoffs]

24:12.874 --> 24:14.441
Shabazz is a good dude, Sarge.

24:14.476 --> 24:16.877
Now listen,
I understand he's in the gang.

24:16.911 --> 24:19.413
But he's just a cat from
the hood that got caught up

24:19.447 --> 24:20.948
doing the wrong thing.
He's not a killer.

24:20.982 --> 24:23.016
Halstead's still under
his cover, it's still good.

24:23.051 --> 24:25.419
- We can get the guns that way.
- No.

24:25.453 --> 24:28.422
I want you staying under, okay?

24:28.456 --> 24:31.125
Until Shabazz actually
moves on his brother,

24:31.159 --> 24:33.327
it's business as usual.

24:34.462 --> 24:36.430
Copy that.

24:36.464 --> 24:39.433
<i>[tense dramatic music]</i>

24:39.467 --> 24:46.707
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:49.010 --> 24:50.611
Hey, hold up. Hold up.

24:50.645 --> 24:53.547
Got a little present for you.

24:53.581 --> 24:55.883
[clears throat]

24:55.917 --> 24:57.451
It's a burner.

24:57.485 --> 24:58.952
So I've been reading your case.

24:58.987 --> 25:00.721
Seems like you're gettin' set up.

25:00.755 --> 25:02.222
They say you're taking the fall

25:02.257 --> 25:04.324
for somebody else
in this Bingham murder.

25:04.359 --> 25:05.959
Point is, if you got a chit to call in

25:05.994 --> 25:07.795
or someone to sell out, you gotta do it,

25:07.829 --> 25:09.463
'cause you're not safe here.

25:09.497 --> 25:11.832
- I'm a big boy.
- Don't matter how big you are,

25:11.866 --> 25:14.768
not in here, not when there's
a target on your back.

25:14.803 --> 25:18.372
Look. I'm just
shooting straight, cop to cop.

25:20.041 --> 25:22.409
But you're not a cop.

25:22.443 --> 25:23.610
'Cause if you were, you'd never say

25:23.645 --> 25:26.547
what you just said.

25:28.616 --> 25:31.485
Sure hope you make bail, Al.

25:31.519 --> 25:38.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:44.232 --> 25:47.167
Bazz, soon as you get this
message, bro, just call me.

25:47.202 --> 25:50.170
Okay? In front of your crib.
This is Lamar, man.

25:50.205 --> 25:51.438
I'm looking for you.

25:51.472 --> 25:53.040
My mind's feelin' a little nervous, dog.

25:53.074 --> 25:55.776
[gunshots]

25:55.810 --> 25:58.378
5021 Ida, emergency. Shots fired

25:58.413 --> 26:01.048
at 1249 South Fillmore,
plain-clothes officers

26:01.082 --> 26:02.482
on the scene.

26:02.517 --> 26:04.051
You hear that?

26:04.085 --> 26:05.953
We up here.

26:05.987 --> 26:07.354
Shabazz!

26:07.388 --> 26:09.656
Hold on, man, hold on.

26:11.426 --> 26:13.193
Got you.

26:13.228 --> 26:15.295
I'm going out the back.

26:15.330 --> 26:19.800
Police! 5021 Ida,
we got a male, black, 6 feet,

26:19.834 --> 26:21.902
black jacket, fleeing in a black SUV.

26:21.936 --> 26:24.972
Can't get plates.
Headed west-bound, down 46th.

26:25.006 --> 26:27.541
Bazz?

26:27.575 --> 26:30.477
- [hisses in pain]
- What happened?

26:30.511 --> 26:32.646
I don't wanna die alone.

26:32.680 --> 26:35.048
Shabazz, who did it?

26:35.083 --> 26:38.218
Wes.

26:38.253 --> 26:40.387
I couldn't do it.

26:40.421 --> 26:43.123
I couldn't kill Malik.

26:44.926 --> 26:47.294
That's because you
a good brother, Shabazz.

26:47.929 --> 26:51.465
[hissing in pain, sobbing]

27:16.391 --> 27:17.925
Shabazz is dead.

27:17.959 --> 27:20.294
- Shabazz, not Malik?
- Just found him in his house

27:20.328 --> 27:22.896
with two in his chest 'cause
he wouldn't kill his brother.

27:22.931 --> 27:24.698
Right before he died,
he told me Wes did it.

27:24.732 --> 27:26.400
I say we go get his ass right now.

27:26.434 --> 27:28.769
Not until we smoke out the M4s.

27:28.803 --> 27:30.704
He's a killer, Sarge.
We got a dead man's word.

27:30.738 --> 27:32.439
Look, we will nail Wes for murder

27:32.473 --> 27:34.441
after we get the guns, understand?

27:34.475 --> 27:36.109
- Hey.
- What?

27:36.144 --> 27:37.911
Dexter just told me
that Wes sent him a picture

27:37.946 --> 27:39.446
of Shabazz with a bullet in his chest.

27:39.480 --> 27:41.248
See, that's proof he delivered his end

27:41.282 --> 27:43.317
of the bargain, which means
the deal's back on.

27:43.351 --> 27:44.952
Yeah, they're meeting at
the old Kagen warehouse

27:44.986 --> 27:46.453
- in an hour.
- All right, get the rest

27:46.487 --> 27:47.654
of the team up to speed.

27:47.689 --> 27:50.724
Let's meet over at the warehouse.

27:50.758 --> 27:52.993
Hey.

27:53.027 --> 27:54.329
You good?

27:55.463 --> 27:57.731
Yeah, I'm good. Let's get 'em.

28:17.659 --> 28:20.493
Okay, I got Halstead
arriving with Dexter.

28:20.527 --> 28:22.583
Just stand by.

28:27.601 --> 28:30.736
No eyes, moving for a better position.

28:31.104 --> 28:33.306
We're in position in the back.

28:34.975 --> 28:37.009
Sarge, this Olinsky thing.

28:37.044 --> 28:39.579
Can't imagine how hard it must be.

28:40.216 --> 28:42.317
- If you need something...
- I just need you

28:42.342 --> 28:44.911
to do your job, Hailey, that's all.

28:49.917 --> 28:53.052
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

28:53.086 --> 28:59.358
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:59.393 --> 29:03.296
Wes is arriving. Wait for my signal.

29:06.461 --> 29:10.335
All right. Game on.
So the guns are here, right?

29:11.804 --> 29:18.776
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:18.811 --> 29:21.569
[whispering] Hell nah.

29:21.601 --> 29:23.602
Whoa.

29:23.636 --> 29:25.104
What's Malik doing here, man?

29:25.138 --> 29:28.774
- Malik?
- Yeah.

29:28.808 --> 29:30.375
He don't know his brother's dead.

29:30.410 --> 29:32.878
Or that he's standing next
to the guy that killed him.

29:32.912 --> 29:36.748
- My man, Wes.
- Hey. You must be Dexter.

29:38.351 --> 29:39.785
What's he doing here?

29:39.819 --> 29:41.887
Oh, that's my business.

29:42.689 --> 29:44.123
He gonna behave himself?

29:44.157 --> 29:47.025
I'm cool as long as you are.

29:50.530 --> 29:52.731
You got the product, man?

29:52.765 --> 29:55.100
You got the money?

29:59.606 --> 30:01.006
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

30:01.040 --> 30:03.709
I need to see the product first.

30:09.449 --> 30:12.251
Come on over. Showtime.

30:16.723 --> 30:18.790
[cell phone ringing]

30:23.196 --> 30:25.597
- No.
- What?

30:27.700 --> 30:29.968
Somebody shot my brother.

30:31.804 --> 30:34.873
I'm sorry to hear that, man.
I really am.

30:34.908 --> 30:38.177
But right now, we got some
business to handle, all right?

30:42.715 --> 30:45.551
What you smirking at?

30:45.585 --> 30:48.820
Nothing.

30:52.091 --> 30:55.827
Sarge, we got a blue van approaching.

30:55.862 --> 30:58.230
Okay, van is approaching, blue.

30:58.264 --> 31:01.533
We wait for it to park
and move in on my signal.

31:01.568 --> 31:04.536
<i>[tense music]</i>

31:04.571 --> 31:11.810
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:16.783 --> 31:18.750
- You mother... you killed...
- Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa!

31:18.785 --> 31:20.686
- [all yelling]
- Take it easy, chill, chill!

31:20.720 --> 31:22.421
Whoa, whoa, we got a gun. Gun, gun, gun.

31:22.455 --> 31:23.488
Move in, now.

31:23.523 --> 31:25.190
Go, go, go.

31:27.527 --> 31:30.562
Chicago PD, don't move!

31:31.464 --> 31:34.499
- Chicago PD, drop your weapon!
- Police! Put it down, Dexter.

31:34.534 --> 31:36.034
Drop the bag.

31:36.069 --> 31:38.604
Antonio, heads-up,
blue van heading your way.

31:38.638 --> 31:45.911
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:46.946 --> 31:48.914
[alarm beeping]

31:59.492 --> 32:01.393
Get out of the van!

32:01.427 --> 32:04.730
Let me see your hands!
Get out of the van!

32:04.764 --> 32:07.199
[gunshots]

32:24.517 --> 32:26.885
Kim! Antonio, are you good?

32:26.919 --> 32:29.421
Yeah, we're good!

32:42.869 --> 32:45.137
Merry Christmas.

32:50.328 --> 32:52.688
- Can't believe you a cop.
- My bad, dog.

32:52.713 --> 32:54.666
It be like that sometimes.

32:55.976 --> 32:57.643
- Who killed my brother?
- You did.

32:57.668 --> 32:59.102
- What?
- You did.

32:59.137 --> 33:00.261
What you talkin' about?
I ain't have nothing

33:00.286 --> 33:01.472
- to do with that.
- Brother, if you would have

33:01.505 --> 33:03.955
kept it 100 from the jump,
and admitted to it,

33:03.979 --> 33:06.205
then Bazz wouldn't be dead.

33:08.040 --> 33:09.908
You would.

33:09.942 --> 33:12.277
Can't put that on me.

33:12.311 --> 33:14.279
I just did.

33:14.313 --> 33:17.315
I just did.

33:17.350 --> 33:24.356
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:28.227 --> 33:29.861
[sighs]

33:29.895 --> 33:31.796
I can't believe we're really here.

33:31.831 --> 33:34.966
Gonna be fine.

33:46.212 --> 33:47.846
Right there.

33:51.350 --> 33:52.984
All rise.

33:53.019 --> 33:54.886
Court is now in session.

33:54.920 --> 33:58.766
The honorable Judge Maddox presiding.

34:01.527 --> 34:03.695
You may be seated.

34:05.765 --> 34:08.667
State of Illinois vs. Alvin Olinsky.

34:08.701 --> 34:15.072
Murder in the second degree,
case #542234.

34:15.107 --> 34:16.416
Mr. Osha?

34:16.487 --> 34:18.789
Your Honor, given the serious
nature of the charge,

34:18.822 --> 34:22.259
and the fact that the defendant
was a veteran police officer

34:22.293 --> 34:24.460
with unique knowledge of
the criminal justice system,

34:24.495 --> 34:27.496
as well as having access
to confidential informants

34:27.524 --> 34:29.658
and members of
organized crime syndicates,

34:29.701 --> 34:32.388
we believe he poses
a significant flight risk.

34:32.467 --> 34:34.435
And as such, we would request that

34:34.469 --> 34:36.304
no bail be set, and that the defendant

34:36.338 --> 34:39.440
be remanded to Cook County Jail
until trial.

34:39.474 --> 34:41.042
Mr. Manetti?

34:41.976 --> 34:44.245
Your Honor, the state's request

34:44.279 --> 34:47.014
is both preposterous and punitive.

34:47.049 --> 34:49.350
This case is built on sand.

34:49.384 --> 34:51.319
The only evidence
connecting Alvin Olinsky

34:51.353 --> 34:53.420
to the homicide victim
is a single strand of hair

34:53.455 --> 34:55.489
and the testimony of
a drug-addled witness.

34:55.524 --> 34:58.025
As such, to hold Mr. Olinsky in prison

34:58.060 --> 34:59.527
to leverage some sort of plea bargain

34:59.561 --> 35:02.296
is unconscionable.
Moreover, Mr. Olinsky's

35:02.331 --> 35:04.365
put his life on the line
for the people of this city

35:04.399 --> 35:06.367
- for over 30 years.
- Mr. Manetti,

35:06.401 --> 35:09.270
this is a bond hearing,
not a closing argument.

35:09.304 --> 35:11.038
Defendant is remanded
into the custody of

35:11.073 --> 35:13.174
the Cook County Jail, pending trial.

35:13.208 --> 35:15.643
- Next case.
- The state of Illinois

35:15.677 --> 35:19.814
vs. Juan Medrano. Aggravated robbery

35:19.848 --> 35:23.451
- Case #3320843.
- Let's go.

35:24.987 --> 35:27.955
<i>[tense music]</i>

35:27.990 --> 35:34.729
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:34.763 --> 35:37.431
- Excuse me, can I help you?
- I got it.

35:38.767 --> 35:41.035
- Where the hell were you?
- Hey, I tried to call you.

35:41.069 --> 35:42.570
We had a deal!

35:42.604 --> 35:44.505
Keep your voice down, for God's sake.

35:44.539 --> 35:46.474
- I did everything that I could.
- Well, it wasn't good enough!

35:46.508 --> 35:48.175
When Judge Gladchuck called in sick,

35:48.210 --> 35:52.346
the Mayor called him, told him
to appoint Judge Maddox.

35:52.381 --> 35:55.149
- The Mayor.
- Yes.

35:56.418 --> 35:59.520
- The Mayor called Gladchuck.
- Yeah.

35:59.554 --> 36:01.756
My guess is, Woods smelled a rat.

36:01.790 --> 36:03.858
Wanted to make sure that he
had the right judge in there

36:03.892 --> 36:05.659
for the bail hearing.

36:06.728 --> 36:10.364
Well... I mean,
can we appeal the ruling?

36:10.399 --> 36:13.234
Yes, but... You know.

36:13.268 --> 36:16.170
Our odds of prevailing
are close to zero.

36:16.204 --> 36:18.506
So Al just stays in custody till trial?

36:18.540 --> 36:21.675
Yeah. Yeah, it's what
the prosecution wants.

36:34.256 --> 36:36.690
[muttering]

36:39.461 --> 36:42.630
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

36:42.664 --> 36:47.935
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:47.969 --> 36:49.937
All right, so what's
the next step, Sarge?

36:49.971 --> 36:51.405
Did you talk to Al or his lawyer?

36:51.440 --> 36:53.707
Is he gonna appeal the bond hearing?

36:54.276 --> 36:56.077
Is he gonna appeal
the bond hearing... Hey!

36:56.111 --> 36:58.512
I asked you a question!

37:04.019 --> 37:05.853
Okay, um...

37:07.355 --> 37:09.824
Al's gonna be out of there.

37:09.858 --> 37:11.592
Soon. Real soon.

37:11.626 --> 37:13.761
- Okay?
- What's that mean?

37:15.797 --> 37:17.631
It means I'm taking care of things,

37:17.666 --> 37:19.767
but I can't get into
the details right now.

37:19.801 --> 37:22.870
Why not?

37:25.140 --> 37:27.741
I appreciate your concern.

37:28.477 --> 37:31.112
But you gotta back off now.

37:31.146 --> 37:33.581
I wanna know what I need
to do to help Al.

37:33.615 --> 37:35.282
And all I'm hearing from you
is nothing...

37:35.317 --> 37:37.518
Because you don't know
what you're talking about!

37:37.552 --> 37:38.986
- Get off! Really?
- Everyone knows...

37:39.020 --> 37:42.022
- Watch yourself!
- Enough! Enough.

37:42.057 --> 37:45.025
<i>[somber music]</i>

37:45.060 --> 37:52.333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:03.311 --> 38:06.280
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

38:06.314 --> 38:12.353
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:12.387 --> 38:14.588
[weary sigh]

38:15.857 --> 38:22.930
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:40.048 --> 38:42.616
<i>[alarm buzzing]</i>

39:17.886 --> 39:20.921
There he is.

39:25.260 --> 39:27.061
Hey!

39:27.095 --> 39:29.930
Not here, not today. Keep moving.

39:29.965 --> 39:32.399
I said, keep moving!

39:51.753 --> 39:53.787
[doorbell rings]

39:53.822 --> 39:56.790
<i>[somber music]</i>

39:56.825 --> 40:03.897
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:16.344 --> 40:18.946
So what's on your mind, Hank?

40:18.980 --> 40:22.249
Olinsky.

40:22.284 --> 40:25.953
It's time to set things straight.

40:29.357 --> 40:31.125
Sounds good to me.

40:31.159 --> 40:33.294
Why don't you walk me through
everything that happened,

40:33.328 --> 40:35.429
from beginning to end.

40:35.463 --> 40:37.364
I will.

40:37.399 --> 40:40.701
First, I want some assurances.

40:40.735 --> 40:44.672
Olinsky is released,
first thing in the morning.

40:44.706 --> 40:47.841
No other charges are filed against him.

40:47.876 --> 40:50.377
Or anyone else.

40:50.412 --> 40:51.879
I can do that...

40:51.913 --> 40:54.315
After I hear what you have to say.

40:54.349 --> 40:57.184
If it's compelling,
I'll call the prosecutor

40:57.218 --> 40:59.520
and we will make it official.

41:03.091 --> 41:05.492
All right, let's do this.

41:11.066 --> 41:13.200
That's why I wanted you
to walk back early, Al.

41:13.234 --> 41:14.635
These guys are animals.

41:14.669 --> 41:17.004
- You okay?
- Yeah, I'm good.

41:17.038 --> 41:18.939
[cell phone vibrating]

41:19.774 --> 41:22.076
Hey.

41:25.714 --> 41:28.649
- [hollers]
- [both men grunting]

